<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1324,1443,1870]" lastBlockId="10.[264,1324,284,590]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,517,1803,1829]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Range extension</emphasis>
: In the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[704,796,1804,1830]" name="Mexico" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[808,1037,1804,1829]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="walkeri">
<emphasis box="[808,1037,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sphaeroma walkeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from the western Florida and Texas coasts (
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley" box="[722,1029,1844,1870]" pageId="9" pageNumber="14" refString="Kensley, B. &amp; Schotte, M. (1989) Guide to the marine isopod crustaceans of the Caribbean. Smithsonian Institution Press, 308 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Kensley &amp; Schotte, 
<number box="[967,1029,1844,1870]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nelson" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="15" refString="Nelson, W. G. &amp; Demetriades, L. (1992) Peracarids associated with sabellariid worm rock (Phragmatopoma lapidosa Kinberg) at Sebastian inlet, Florida, U. S. A. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 12 (4), 647 - 654." type="journal article" year="1992">
Nelson &amp; Demetriades, 
<number box="[264,327,284,310]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The presence of 
<taxonomicName box="[565,689,284,309]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="walkeri">
<emphasis box="[565,689,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">S. walkeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at SM inlet, extends its geographic distribution to Tamaulipas State, 
<collectingCountry box="[480,574,324,350]" name="Mexico" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1324,284,590]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,426,363,389]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species has mangrove roots and dead trees as preferred habitats (
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley" pageId="10" pageNumber="14" refString="Kensley, B., Nelson, W. G. &amp; Schotte, M. (1995) Marine isopod biodiversity of the Indian River Lagoon, Florida. Bulletin of Marine Science, 57 (1), 136 - 142." type="journal article" year="1995">
Kensley 
<emphasis box="[319,370,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[385,447,404,430]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but may also be associated with colonies of sabellariid worms (
<bibRefCitation author="Nelson" pageId="10" pageNumber="15" refString="Nelson, W. G. &amp; Demetriades, L. (1992) Peracarids associated with sabellariid worm rock (Phragmatopoma lapidosa Kinberg) at Sebastian inlet, Florida, U. S. A. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 12 (4), 647 - 654." type="journal article" year="1992">
Nelson &amp; Demetriades, 
<number box="[427,490,444,470]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It occurs in marine, shallow, intertidal warm waters and probably it is limited to a pantropical distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley" box="[695,994,484,510]" pageId="10" pageNumber="14" refString="Kensley, B. &amp; Schotte, M. (1989) Guide to the marine isopod crustaceans of the Caribbean. Smithsonian Institution Press, 308 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Kensley &amp; Schotte, 
<number box="[932,994,484,510]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley" box="[1006,1070,484,510]" pageId="10" pageNumber="14" refString="Kensley, B. &amp; Schotte, M. (2000) World list of marine and freswater Crustacea Isopoda. Smithsonian Institution, 106 p. Gopher: // nmnhgoph. si. edu / 00 /. docs / isoaqua _ info / about." type="book" year="2000">
<number box="[1006,1070,484,510]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1324,284,590]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
